I saw the rating of this game and decided it would be worth one dollar to try, and it was. The graphics are good as far as detailing of individual creatures and structures go, but the world itself is too open/lacks detail and is pretty poorly structured. I love how the dragons level and unlock a lot of different things; it makes the game feel more custom, though I would like different body types to the dragons versus just changing horns and colors. I rated the different aspects of the game 4/5, but the real problem is the glitching. Dragons glitching through the ground (babies are basically broken), dragons floating and spazzing out while they eat, and animals/people freaking out when you grab them. Other than that, I like the promise this game holds if the bugs get fixed and the world is more refined.

This is an amazing game!! It's especially incredible for a $0.99 phone app! Being able to embody a dragon and do dragon things is all I've ever wanted in a game, and this simulator fulfills that dream for me! I was surprised about how sophisticated the game is. You can level your dragon, choose which element you want to master (either fire, ice, or storm), fight bosses, collect gold, purchase dragon upgrades (with the in game currency, of course!) and become allies with other dragons! If you take your allies out of the lair with you, then they will level with you. You can also swap between your dragon followers and level them and their stats as well. Curious about the other breath elements? No problem! Just give your followers the powers of the other elements and you can have all three! Also, there are three inhabitable layers and you can live in any of them! There's a button you can tap to switch to another lair if you're currently sitting in that lair.  I know this is a rather long review, but all in all: there's so much to this game and it's SO INCREDIBLY worth it!! I'm surprised it does only cost $0.99! I highly recommend this game!! Thank you so much, Gluten Free Games!
